<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 32 (July 9th, 2014)</h4><ul><li>A melee Shaper's creep score in the Scoreboard will be incremented by one for every two stacks of melee Gladiator passive that they consume.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The mechanic for gaining stacking bonus Vim for consecutive last hits has been removed from the game.</li><li>Gladiators will now gain a flat 200% increased Vim for scoring the killing blow on a minion.</li><li>Melee Shapers using the Gladiator role will store 50% of the total Vim a nearby minion is worth if they fail to kill it. On the next minion kill you will gain any stored bonus Vim you have accrued this way. This can be stored up to a maximum of 3 times.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 1 (June 06, 2013)</h4><ul><li>Bonus vim per stack acquired from consecutive last hits reduced to 2, down from 3.</li></ul>